Governor of Rivers State, Nysesom Wike has awarded the players and managers of the Rivers United with a state medal, gifting each of them a sum of $20,000 for winning the 2021/22 Nigerian Professional Football League (NPFL) title. Recall that the Rivers United last weekend defeated visiting Gombe United, taking home the trophy. The Governor hosted the players and officials at the Government House on Thursday. Wike who was impressed by their performance, promised that they would be sent to spend two weeks in Madrid to prepare for the next seasonâ€™s CAF Champions League.